            "id": "4580256",
            "title": "Nvidia chief accounting officer to retire, set to be replaced by former Intel exec",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Nvidia (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/NVDA\" title=\"NVIDIA Corporation\">NVDA</a></span>) disclosed on Monday that Donald Robertson, vice president and chief accounting officer, is set to retire from the company, effective May 4.</li>\n<li>Robertson will remain with Nvidia as VP, Finance to support various projects until July 1, the company <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/filing/268601038\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"added\">added</a>. He will be replaced by former Intel (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/INTC\" title=\"Intel Corporation\">INTC</a></span>) chief accounting officer Scott Gawel, who <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/news/4579887-intel-says-its-chief-accounting-officer-has-resigned\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"resigned\">resigned</a> from the company this past Friday.</li>\n<li>Gawel will have a base salary of $800,000 and will be granted two new hire equity grants of restricted stock units with a combined target value of $12.875M. The RSUs will vest approximately over a four-year period according to Nvidia's standard vesting schedules. </li>\n<li>Nvidia shares gained nearly 4% on Monday, while Intel shares added 2%.</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
