        {
            "id": "4580219",
            "title": "Amkor declines after Q1 results feature 27% revenue jump",
            "description": "<html><body><p data-eci=\"true\">Amkor Technology (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\"><a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/AMKR\" title=\"Amkor Technology, Inc.\">AMKR</a></span>) shares declined during early post-market trading on Monday after it released its first quarter 2026 financial results.</p>\n<p>For the quarter ended March 31, the semiconductor packaging and test services company reported earnings per share of $0.33 versus the consensus estimate of $0.24.</p>\n<p>Revenue for the quarter increased 27% year over year to $1.68B, which was more than the $1.65B estimate.</p>\n<p>Looking ahead, Amkor expects its second-quarter sales to range from $1.75B to $1.85B, which clears the $1.74B estimate. It expects net income ranging from $105M to $130M and EPS of $0.42 to $0.52. It provided guidance of 14.5% to 15.5% for its gross margin.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, it projects its 2026 capital expenditures to range from $2.5B to $3B.</p>\n<p><span>The company paid a quarterly dividend of $0.08352 per share on March 31. Last week, the Board of Directors authorized the repurchase of up to $300M of the company's common stock.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>\"Amkor delivered a strong start to 2026 with record first-quarter revenue driven by broad-based end market demand,\" said CEO </span><span class=\"person\">Kevin Engel. \"During the quarter, we progressed key customer programs in advanced packaging, improved utilization across our factory network, and made continued progress on our margin initiatives, demonstrating our ability to execute effectively in a dynamic industry environment.\"</span></span></p>\n<div class=\"signup_widget_placeholder\"></div>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
            "link": "https://seekingalpha.com/news/4580219-amkor-declines-after-q1-results-feature-27-revenue-jump",
            "pub_date": "2026-04-28 04:19:05",
            "source": "seekalpha",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
